  <section id="products">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Our flagship devices</h2>
      <p class="section-sub">
        Two practical innovations designed to improve safety, positioning and workflow during veterinary procedures.
      </p>

      <div class="grid2">

        <div class="card product">
          <img src="/petholder_product.png" alt="" class="product-bg" aria-hidden="true" />
          <span class="product-kicker">Positioning & restraint support</span>
          <h3>PetHolder</h3>
          <p style="font-weight:500;color:var(--text);margin:4px 0 10px;font-size:15px;">
            A suction-based positioning device designed to stabilise sedated animals during examinations and procedures.
          </p>
          <p style="color:var(--muted);margin:0;font-weight:300;line-height:1.6">
            PetHolder helps veterinary teams position sedated animals more securely while reducing manual restraint.
            It supports safer, more consistent handling during imaging, examinations and selected minor procedures.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Helps reduce repeated staff handling during procedures.</li>
            <li>Supports stable positioning for sedated animals.</li>
            <li>Useful for radiography, examinations and selected minor interventions.</li>
            <li>Adheres to smooth, non-porous surfaces such as glass, stainless steel, metal and plastic.</li>
            <li>Holding force up to 5–10 kg per suction cup depending on surface conditions.</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="cta">
            <a class="btn primary" href="/en/PetHolder.html">View PetHolder</a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card product">
          <img src="/petanesth_product.png" alt="" class="product-bg" aria-hidden="true" />
          <span class="product-kicker">Anaesthesia workflow support</span>
          <h3>PetAnesth</h3>
          <p style="font-weight:500;color:var(--text);margin:4px 0 10px;font-size:15px;">
            A dedicated support system for veterinary anaesthesia circuits.
          </p>
          <p style="color:var(--muted);margin:0;font-weight:300;line-height:1.6">
            PetAnesth helps secure the breathing circuit, reduce unwanted traction on the endotracheal tube
            and improve operating room organisation during anaesthetic procedures.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Improves anaesthetic workflow and circuit stability.</li>
            <li>Helps reduce traction on the endotracheal tube.</li>
            <li>Keeps the surgical area clearer and better organised.</li>
            <li>Replaces improvised solutions with a more consistent setup.</li>
            <li>Quick attachment to veterinary tables up to 5 cm thick.</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="cta">
            <a class="btn primary" href="/en/PetAnesth.html">View PetAnesth</a>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
